    <bioghist>Adrian, Michigan, lawyer; editor of Grange newspaper, The Michigan Patron, Democratic state senator, 1899-1903, and Republican state representative, 1931-1938.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Correspondence and business papers concerning farming and Grange affairs, legal business and Michigan politics; also material on the 1918 U.S. senatorial campaign in which Helme was a Democratic candidate in the primary election; and copies of articles and speeches, diary of everyday events in 1882, and scrapbooks of clippings on campaign activities, with notes by Helme. Correspondents include Woodbridge Ferris (Nov. 4 and Nov. 14, 1912) and Laura Haviland (undated).</scopecontent>
